programme.title: Martial Arts History Museum-Cynthia Rothrock
programme.desc: Officially named, “Queen of the Martial Arts,” Cynthia Rothrock is considered one of the most historic figures in martial arts history. or five consecutive years, she was the undefeated World Champion in the karate tournament circuit. She has graced the cover of over 60 martial arts magazines and was inducted into the prestigious Martial Arts History Museum’s Hall of Fame at its inception in 1999. In the 1980s, she became one of the biggest box office draws in both Hong Kong and America for her action films. To date, she has starred in over 60 films and was also named “Queen of the Martial Arts in Films”. She continues to be one of the greatest advocates for the martial arts conducting countless seminars throughout the world.

programme.title: Martial Arts History Museum-Gerald Okamura
programme.desc: Officially called the "scariest man alive" by Black Belt magazine, we go behind the scenes of one of the most awesome Asian bad guys, Gerald Okamura. From his iconic role at the Hatchett Man in "Big Trouble in Little China," to his many appearances as an evil bad dude, we explore Gerald Okamura's history, his life and his legendary career as one of the top weapons experts in America. Gerald Okamura was inducted into the Martial Arts History Museum's Hall of Fame in 2003. Directed by William Ford with Director of Photography Jim Towns.

programme.title: Flash Legs
programme.desc: A band of thieves, known as the Eight Dragons, commit murder in the process of a stealing a treasure map. They decide three years is long enough for the heat to die down and allow them to search for their hidden fortune. But none of the thieves trusts any of his brothers-in-crime to keep the map that long. Their leader's solution is to cut the map into eight pieces, one for each bandit. Meanwhile, a pair of relentless lawmen is after them. One policeman is killed in their battle with the first bandit they find. The remaining cop, Fong Yee, is all the more determined to hunt down the other seven. One by one, he collects the pieces of the map as his flashy, flashing feet kick his opponents into submission or death.

For trivia buffs: Legendary director George Cuckor went uncredited on this feature, though he stepped in to guide several scenes after official director Edward Griffith walked off the production.

programme.title: The Admiral Was A Lady (1950)
programme.desc: In this laugh-a-minute, post-World War II comedy, Wanda Hendrix (Prince of Foxes) stars as Jean Madison, a former WAVE (Women Accepted for Volunteer Emergency Service) ensign taken under the wings of a rowdy group of former airmen, who affectionately dub her the “Admiral.” Handily directed by veteran filmmaker Albert S. Rogell (Li’l Abner), the film is bolstered by the crackling chemistry between Hendrix and her co-star, Oscar winner Edmond O’Brien (The Barefoot Contessa).

programme.title: Hoppy Serves a Writ
programme.desc: Sheriff Hopalong Cassidy triumphs again in this lighthearted western romp from Harry Sherman Productions. Good ol' Happy (William Boyd) has to leave his beloved Texas to track down some bad guys in Oklahoma. You can bet that the action and suspense will follow Hopalong wherever he goes. Also, look for a number of familiar faces in the ast, including TV's future Superman George Reeves, notorious Hollywood heavy Victor Jory, and in his movie debut, Robert Mitchum!

programme.title: Too Late for Tears (1949)
programme.desc: Lizabeth Scott turned in what many consider her finest role in this shocking noir about a woman who finds herself in possession of stolen money. When a dangerous character named Danny Fuller (Dan Duryea) tracks her down and claims the money is his, she’s determined to hang onto her stash. Director Byron Haskin (I Walk Alone) brings together a fine cast that includes Don Defore and Arthur Kennedy, plus cinematography by two-time Oscar winner William C. Mellor (A Place in the Sun). If you’ve never seen this noir gem, you’re in for a hard­boiled treat!

programme.title: Curse of the Doll People
programme.desc: A group of tourists in Mexico are sent masked living dolls as messengers of death.

programme.title: Speed Devils
programme.desc: Racecar drivers-turned-business partners Marty and Dan run a successful auto repair shop, but run into trouble when Marty refuses to accept repair jobs from the city to spite two crooked politicians. The politicians attempt to drive a wedge between the partners by using Dan's girlfriend Pat to conconct a fictional love triangle between the three...which may or may not be based in reality!

programme.title: Carol Burnett Show - Season 1 Episode 1
programme.desc: Guest starring Jim Nabors along with a variety of skits including a `V.I.P' interview with Shirley Dimple, Jim and Carol as two misfit skiers in `The Ski Lodge', the first `Carol and Sis' sketch, and a Broadway medley. Jim sings `You Don't Have to Say You Love Me' in Italian, and Carol as the Charwoman sings `Georgy Girl'.

programme.title: Season 28 Episode 259
programme.desc: Comedian Johnny Carson hosts a variety of celebrities in his iconic late night talk show.

programme.title: Mesa of Lost Women
programme.desc: Spider-women lure men to their death in this thriller from the golden era of Drive-in schlock! This story of a mad scientist (Jackie Coogan) is regarded as one of the worst movies ever made. Still, dig the crazy guitar and piano score which was purloined by Ed Wood Jr. for Jail Bait, and notice a couple of Wood regulars (Dolores Fuller and Lyle Talbot) in the credits. What you have here is a sort of cousin to the films of Ed Wood, but one that can stand on its own as being truly awful. Enjoy!

programme.title: The Monster Walks (1932)
programme.desc: Trapped in a house on a dark, stormy night with a killer ape! Returning to her recently deceased father’s sizable estate to read his last will and testament, Ruth Earlton (Vera Reynolds) and her fiancé are horrified to discover that the basement is occupied by a massive, hideous ape that was subjected to experimentation by her father. And although Ruth is given control of her late father’s estate, she soon finds herself the prime target of the mutated simian—and possibly the nefarious housekeepers, bitter about their meager share of their former master’s fortune. Featuring a compelling turn from Oscar Nominee Mischa Auer (My Man Godfrey) and helmed by genre B-Movie maestro Frank R. Strayer (The Vampire Bat), The Monster Walks is a chilling and mysterious master class in eeriness.

programme.title: Attack of the Mayan Mummy
programme.desc: Following the death of his sister, who was co-director with him of the Cowan Research Center in Pasadena, Dr. Frederick Munson was ousted and replaced by his widowed brother-in-law, Dr. Edmund Redding. Through Redding's son, Timmy, Munson has been able to learn of a secret project at the institute involving the use of hypnosis to regress subjects to past lives, which information Munson passes along to a friend, Dr. John Janney. (BW)

programme.title: Man with Two Lives
programme.desc: The soul of an executed criminal finds its way into the body of a man brought back from death in this thriller from Hollywood’s Poverty Row. Director Phil Rosen (Charlie Chan in the Secret Service) weaves a spine-tingling story with help from a great cast, including Edward Norris (Boy’s Town, Decoy) Marlo Dwyer (The Sniper, Crossfire) and Kenne Duncan (Night of the Ghouls, The Sinister Urge).

programme.title: Man Beast
programme.desc: Connie Hayward mounts an expedition into the Himalayan Mountains looking for her brother, who has not returned from a previous trek trying to locate the Yeti, or "Abominable Snowman". Arriving at her brother's last-known camp Connie and her companions find only a strange old guide, Varga. They are soon attacked by gigantic Snowmen but are not half as surprised as when Vargas reveals his secret origin and the plans he has for Connie.

programme.title: Skin (1961)
programme.desc: Here he is: the one, the only… GROUCHO! Legendary comedian, Groucho Marx, hosts this laugh-a-minute quiz show, where three couples face off, answering questions of varying difficulty. This game show is sure to make you laugh as contestants struggle to keep up with Marx’s lightning-quick wit and goofy antics.

programme.title: The Big Seventeen
programme.desc: Upper middle-class teenagers in Los Angeles are going crazy. They trash a movie theater, beating up the manager and pushing a young man through a plate glass window. Sergeant Friday must get to the bottom of what is causing this to happen.

programme.title: Front Runner (1959)
programme.desc: Two rival jockeys faceoff at the racetrack, but one of them may have an advantage after an unexpected run in with the supernatural.

programme.title: Face of Murder (1959)
programme.desc: Mike sets up an interview with a man who has been convicted of five murders and is currently waiting for his scheduled execution. When the two meet, the prisoner makes an escape attempt and takes Mike and a priest hostage.

programme.title: Death at Dawn
programme.desc: After Farmer Perkins murders a store clerk in front of his wife, and is allowed to walk after his trial, the Cartwright's step in to make sure he'll be rearrested, tried, and hung.

programme.title: Jed Buys the Freeway
programme.desc: Henry Jones shows up at the Clampett's pretending to be an old friend.

programme.title: The Case of the Jolly Hangman
programme.desc: A traveling salesman is found hanged in his hotel room. The police eventually rule it to be a suicide, but his widow thinks otherwise, and asks Holmes to investigate the further.

programme.title: Breath of Life
programme.desc: Medic follows Dr. Konrad Styner and his team of Surgeons as they tackle medical cases inside Los Angeles.

programme.title: Four the Hard Way
programme.desc: New York City police officer Barney Ruditsky faces off against organized crime during the Roaring 20s.

programme.title: Folk Song Festival
programme.desc: When the hotel hosts a children's song festival, Stanley takes charge of the Italian group.

programme.title: The Matchmaker
programme.desc: The Andersons host a party for Margaret's cousin Louise and her boyfriend Tom, hoping there is a proposal in the future.

programme.title: Bad Man of Deadwood (1941)
programme.desc: Roy Rogers and Gabby Hayes are together again in this Republic Pictures gem. This time they’re trying to set up a medicine show in Deadwood, a town known for dangerous entrepreneurs who don’t like competition. Sally Payne is on-hand as a member of the troop where Roy and Gabby work as entertainers, while Carol Adams plays a reporter who may have a romantic interest in Roy. Songs include ‘Song of the Dusty Trail’, and ‘Home on the Rangeland’.

programme.title: Report from the Aleutians
programme.desc: A filmic record of US military operations on the Aleutian Island of Adak to take back Japanese occupied Kiska. Though uncredited, John Huston (The Maltese Falcon) directed this documentary, which also features music by four time Oscar winner Dimitri Tiomkin (High Noon, The Old Man and the Sea). Director Huston, who also helped narrate the film and was actually in the Army Signal Corps at the time of filming, wanted to use this documentary to show the everyday life of American soldiers. Though the US Army initially objected, Huston got his way...

programme.title: The Road to Hollywood (1947)
programme.desc: Bing Crosby fans will be intrigued by this selection of scenes from early Crosby shorts woven together to create a fictional biography of one Hollywood’s biggest stars. Director Bud Pollard appears as the narrator, while the king of the crooners sings such songs as ‘One More Chance’, and ‘Wrap Your troubles in Dreams’.

programme.title: Renegade Girl
programme.desc: Ann Shelby, who's family is allied with the notorious William Quantrill, lives life as an outlaw to exact revenge on the murder of her brother.

programme.title: The Fabulous Dorseys (1947)
programme.desc: Tommy and Jimmy Dorsey play themselves in this high-spirited film biography. The film follows the brothers from their early days all the way to their greatest successes. Director Alfred E. Green ("The Jolson Story") uses the film as a showcase for some great music, including "I'm Getting Sentimental Over You" and "Marie." Jazz buffs will notice cameos by such greats as bandleader Paul Whiteman and pianist Art Tatum. In fact, look for a special jam session featuring the Dorseys and Tatum. It's a perfect snapshot of the days when musicians could really swing.

programme.title: Hazel's People (Happy as the Grass Was Green)
programme.desc: A Mennonite boy is beaten to death at an unnamed NY university protesting the Vietnam War. His best friend and another college student, Eric Mills, attends his funeral in the Mennonite country in Pennsylvania.

programme.title: International Crime (1938)
programme.desc: A multifaceted mystery full of shocking twists and turns, this is one of the earliest onscreen appearances of the detective figure known as “The Shadow.” The story follows Lamont Cranston (Rod La Rocque), an amateur criminologist and detective who gets tangled up in a web of deception and danger when he sets out to capture an infamous safe cracker. A wildly popular print and radio character birthed in pulp novels of the 1930s, The Shadow left such an enduring impression on the American public that he spawned a film adaptation starring Alec Baldwin more than 60 years after the character’s genesis.

programme.title: Torture Ship
programme.desc: This low budget screamer from Sigmund Neufeld Productions stars Lyle Talbot and Irving Pichel in a story of a mad scientist performing cruel experiments on board his private ship. His plan is to learn about the criminal mind, and what better way than to...well, you know. Obviously, this isn’t the Love Boat! Victor Halperin (White Zombie) directed this tale based on a story by none other than Jack London. Sit back and enjoy. Just don’t let the man with the scalpel near your head!

programme.title: Episode 5
programme.desc: Groucho, Chico and Harpo graced the small screen in the 1950s appearing in a myriad of variety programs, sitcoms, and game shows. The Marx Brothers TV Collection features long-lost material from this wide array of appearances.

Megan received a special phone call from her grandma, though, that she'll remember forever. Mila Jam had it all, or so she thought. Her drag persona, Britney Houston, had a massive YouTube following and she performed on a hit TV show in London. But she gave it all up so that she could finally live her truth as a woman and as herself. Olivia Page was brave enough to transition in high school. Unfortunately, a classmate decided to cyberbully her on Facebook. Olivia also had the support and kindness of a teacher who helped her through high school. A wild series of events led Sam to meeting the love of her life. Andre J. wants to tell you one thing: Love Yourself. programme.title: The Guys Next Door
programme.desc: Who, among us, can say that we come from a “normal” family? The Guys Next Door, a feature length documentary, offers an alternative to the traditional ideas of what constitute the nuclear American family. Meet Erik and Sandro, a gay couple with two daughters birthed by their friend Rachel with donor eggs. In her 40s, Rachel is married to Tony and they have three biological children of their own. Rachel and Tony, a seemingly traditional married couple, live in the suburbs of Massachusetts with their children. Inspired by a TV program about the difficulties and costs associated with gay couples having children, Rachel, age 41, volunteers to be a surrogate – not once, but twice within two years – for Erik, her good friend from college, and his husband Sandro, an Italian émigré. This film begins when Rachel is eight months pregnant with Erik and Sandro’s second daughter, Eleonora. What compels a woman in her forties with three children of her own to carry children for friends? What is the reaction of her husband and children? And, how will Erik and Sandro handle the challenges of parenting two girls in a world that still emphasizes the importance of maternal instinct? The issues raised in this film - gay marriage and parenting, surrogacy as a path for gays and lesbians to have children, and the extension and redefinition of what it means to be “an American family" - remain relevant as our country is a cultural battleground during the divisive 2016 presidential election. The Guys Next Door is a powerful antidote to the negative backlash and hateful rhetoric aimed at same sex families. In the words of the esteemed documentary filmmaker Ross McElwee (Sherman’s March), “with nuance, verve and humor, this film goes well beyond issues of surrogacy and gay parenthood and explores the humanity that connects us all."

programme.title: Were You Gay In High School?
programme.desc: Two queer women recall their awkward, closeted high school days of kissing boys and straight-girl crushes.

programme.title: TransMilitary
programme.desc: The 2018 SXSW Audience Award-winning feature film debut by Gabriel Silverman, Fiona Dawson, & Jamie Coughlin, TransMilitary follows the Emmy-nominated short film Transgender, at War and in Love. Around 15,500 transgender people serve in the U.S. military (notably the largest transgender employer in the U.S.), where they must conceal their gender identity because military policies ban their service. TransMilitary chronicles the lives of four individuals (Senior Airman Logan Ireland, Corporal Laila Villanueva, Captain Jennifer Peace & First Lieutenant El Cook) defending their country’s freedom while fighting for their own. They put their careers and their families’ livelihoods on the line by coming out as transgender to top brass officials in the Pentagon in hopes of attaining the equal right to serve. The ban was lifted in 2016, but with President Trump now trying to reinstate it, their futures hang in the balance once again.

programme.title: Her Story
programme.desc: S1 | Her Story is about two trans women in Los Angeles who have given up on love, when chance encounters give them hope. Violet is drawn to Allie, a reporter who approaches her for an interview. Career-driven Paige meets James, the first man she's considered opening up to in years. Will they risk letting what they are stand in the way of being loved for who they are? This is a story of complex characters who laugh, struggle, and grow, who share strength in sisterhood, who seek and find love. Her Story depicts the unique, complicated, and very human women we see in queer communities, and explores how these women navigate the intersections of label identity and love.

programme.title: Ann
programme.desc: Ann is a feature film narrating the story of Ruben, a visual artist who has decided to abandon his tormented life by taking refuge within his own imagination; creating a world parallel to reality.

programme.title: The Kinsey Sicks: Almost Infamous
programme.desc: The Kinsey Sicks are back with their show on the road to Vegas or Bust. This time America’s Favorite Dragapella Group are out to prove that they’ve got the biggest busts and bigger voices in the City of Sin.

programme.title: Engaged
programme.desc: ENGAGED is a short romantic comedy that follows Darren (Daniel K. Isaac), who keeps trying – and failing – to propose to his boyfriend Elliot (Ryan Jamaal Swain). When their relationship is put into an uncomfortable spotlight during a friend’s outrageous engagement party, Darren realizes he actually might be self–sabotaging himself due to unresolved insecurities about his sexuality.

programme.title: Showtime: A Coming Of Age Football Story
programme.desc: A powerful story of the 2019 Parkway North Junior Vikings 8th Grade Team as they strive to become 3 time champions. Despite their differences while learning life lessons through the game of football join together as one team, one vision, one community.

programme.title: Political Animals
programme.desc: Political Animals celebrates the legendary civil rights victories of four trailblazing California state politicians: Carole Migden, Sheila Keuhl, Jackie Goldberg, and Christine Kehoe. Fierce and unrelenting, these courageous women toppled a partisan majority and emerged victors to pass historic legislation for social justice and LGBT+ equality. It was a hard fight – filled with vehemently heated debates and hateful insults hurled by opponents. Today, the message behind Political Animals is more important than ever as the current political theatre unfurls around the globe. These inspiring biographies further reveal the critical importance for public resistance at the local level to pressure lawmakers to enact difficult change. Political Animals is a clear call to action for a new era of greater democratic participation. We invite you to follow in the footsteps of these historic leaders and become the next pioneering political animal!

programme.title: Ti@s
programme.desc: Inspired by the discrimination suffered by his uncle Ramón because of his sexual condition, John Petrizzelli uses the screen to narrate the lives of different people who have something in common: sexual-diversity.

programme.title: The Q Agenda
programme.desc: S2 E7 | In this episode of The Q Agenda we're joined by LGBTQ activist Diego Sepulveda to talk about the Democratic Primary, musician Tom Goss, and gay role models for children. Don't people have better things to worry about instead of Billy Porter being on Sesame Street?

programme.title: The Q Agenda
programme.desc: S2 E8 | In this episode, we're joined by Queer Eye OG/actor Jai Rodriguez, Inside Edition correspondent Victoria Recaño, and we discuss the anti-trans legislation known as The Vulnerable Children Act. All that and more on The Q Agenda!

programme.title: Denial
programme.desc: DENIAL is a documentary about electricity, identity, family, and about the many ways we lie to ourselves when faced with overwhelming facts. It is the story of a family coming to terms with complex personal truths against the backdrop of a global crisis.

programme.title: Putting On
programme.desc: S2 E1 | While On is working on his new MO underwear collection and traveling to Los Angeles to do press for his show, his fiancé struggles to navigate a broken justice system in an effort to find out more details about the end of his parole program since On’s dreams of a perfect wedding depend on it.

programme.title: Putting On
programme.desc: S2 E2 | On meets with his perfume factory before traveling to Tel Aviv for a photoshoot and clothing line collaboration. Meanwhile, we get to know a bit more about his fiancée and his connection to personal training. On is encouraging Dave to open his own gym and dream big.

programme.title: Putting On
programme.desc: S2 E3 | As their time in NYC comes to a close, On dives deeper into his work while trying to close last minute details on a wedding ceremony in Paris. The couple find time to do one last food run, muckbanging their favorite food spots around the city.

programme.title: Jonathan's Kitchen
programme.desc: S1 E1 | Farm market owner Debra Moser joins me as we prepare the first sweet, crisp asparagus of the season.

programme.title: Jonathan's Kitchen
programme.desc: S1 E2 | After meeting Soraya Aguilar at her oil and vinegar store we head home to the kitchen to make a vinaigrette.

programme.title: The Guys Next Door
programme.desc: Who, among us, can say that we come from a “normal” family? The Guys Next Door, a feature length documentary, offers an alternative to the traditional ideas of what constitute the nuclear American family. Meet Erik and Sandro, a gay couple with two daughters birthed by their friend Rachel with donor eggs. In her 40s, Rachel is married to Tony and they have three biological children of their own. Rachel and Tony, a seemingly traditional married couple, live in the suburbs of Massachusetts with their children. Inspired by a TV program about the difficulties and costs associated with gay couples having children, Rachel, age 41, volunteers to be a surrogate – not once, but twice within two years – for Erik, her good friend from college, and his husband Sandro, an Italian émigré. This film begins when Rachel is eight months pregnant with Erik and Sandro’s second daughter, Eleonora. What compels a woman in her forties with three children of her own to carry children for friends? What is the reaction of her husband and children? And, how will Erik and Sandro handle the challenges of parenting two girls in a world that still emphasizes the importance of maternal instinct? The issues raised in this film - gay marriage and parenting, surrogacy as a path for gays and lesbians to have children, and the extension and redefinition of what it means to be “an American family" - remain relevant as our country is a cultural battleground during the divisive 2016 presidential election. The Guys Next Door is a powerful antidote to the negative backlash and hateful rhetoric aimed at same sex families. In the words of the esteemed documentary filmmaker Ross McElwee (Sherman’s March), “with nuance, verve and humor, this film goes well beyond issues of surrogacy and gay parenthood and explores the humanity that connects us all."

programme.title: Happy Playland
programme.desc: S1 E1-5 | Billie Haare, an anxious actress caught between her passion for stage and her parents’ dreams of the silver screens, starts a new job at a desolate indoor playground, managed by wannabe-insta-star Cris. Billie quickly develops feelings for social justice warrior, Zara, who is sadly 23 and not looking for anything serious. After a passionate moment in the ball pit, Billie and Zara both begin to question what they want. But the playland is soon to be closed - and Billie’s anxiety can only handle so much. Cris decides to intervene. Can Billie woo Zara into forever and always? Will anyone ned up happy? Will Cris’ trip to Queenstown increase her followers? Only time will tell, in the place where dreams come true, Happy Playland, The Wellington branch.

programme.title: Happy Playland
programme.desc: S1 E6-10 | Billie Haare, an anxious actress caught between her passion for stage and her parents’ dreams of the silver screens, starts a new job at a desolate indoor playground, managed by wannabe-insta-star Cris. programme.title: (A)Sexual
programme.desc: Facing a sex obsessed culture, a mountain of stereotypes and misconceptions, and a lack of social or scientific research, asexuals – people who experience no sexual attraction -- struggle to claim their identity.

programme.title: Change in The Family
programme.desc: This documentary chronicles the transgender-transition of Zo Thorpe and the sympathetic response of his family. This is a story of celebration, health, and unconditional love. A much-needed portrayal of trans and gender-nonconforming lives in America.

programme.title: I Do
programme.desc: A gay Briton living in New York risks losing his family and residency in the United States. He marries a lesbian friend to remain in the country, but things get complicated when he meets the love of his life.↵

programme.title: Gayborhood
programme.desc: S1 E1 | Adrian’s event doesn’t go as expected. Leacy prepares a first date. Sethe unveils his new art installation and it leaves D’ante with questions. Casey’s hook up isn’t quite what he expected and Blaine has problems adjusting.

programme.title: Gayborhood
programme.desc: S1 E2 | S*@% goes down with Casey and the group is left trying to pick up the pieces.

programme.title: Sink Sank Sunk
programme.desc: Sink Sank Sunk is a digital triptych that tells the story of Cooper, a young gay recluse with some unresolved mommy issues. In this Revry Original digital series, Cooper journeys to complete his late-mother's passion project, a documentary about her synchronized swimming team, venturing into the unfamiliar waters of community, empathy, and romantic love. Sink Sank Sunk is a tender and playful meditation on being a part of something bigger than yourself.

programme.title: Culture Q
programme.desc: Culture Q is the world’s first weekly queer-centric news series brought to you by the leading global queer streaming network, Revry. This innovative, weekly news series creatively features entertainment, pop culture, lifestyle and political news with wit and insightfully nuanced perspectives. Emphasizing the queer millieu, Culture Q stands to be the leading, weekly forum for boundary-pushing discussions and commentary. Hosted by digital news influencer pioneers, Shira Lazar and Andy Lalwani of the highly successful What’s Trending, Culture Q will feature an ever-changing cavalcade of guests who help capture that X-factor which defines queer culture.

programme.title: Magic H8 Ball
programme.desc: Burned by a cheating boyfriend (and some mild chlamydia), a heartbroken pushover turns to a mysterious Magic 8 Ball for the answers. But as he starts giving into his impulses, he risks his hurt turning into hate-and losing all control.

programme.title: Your Eyes On Me
programme.desc: Your Eyes on Me is a story about a drag queen named Gloria whose life changes when she meets Kandi, a drag virgin auditioning for her next show. As the bond develops between the two, their relationship takes an unexpected turn. Suddenly the past and the choices Gloria made as a young man become a stark reality.

programme.title: For Izzy
programme.desc: The lives of a recovering queer addict and her single mother change forever when they move in next door to a widowed father and his adult daughter with autism.

programme.title: CONTRACORRIENTE
programme.desc: Miguel is a fisherman in a tiny Peruvian village where traditions run deep. He is married to the lovely Mariela and about to be a father, but has a secret love affair with Santiago, a painter, who is ostracized by the town because he's gay. After a tragic accident occurs, Miguel must choose between sentencing Santiago to eternal torment or doing right by him and, in turn, revealing their relationship to Mariela and the entire village.

programme.title: Meet Clean Green Certified Founder Chris Van Hook
programme.desc: Certification for sustainable, naturally-grown agriculture, Clean Green Certified is the closest to “Organic” that the cannabiz can get. We're honored to welcome founder Chris Van Hook. Together, we explore the value of certification for industry operators, consumers and the planet. Chris offers tips and tricks that you can put to use in your own garden. Dig in! Founded in 2004, Swami Select has had the pleasure of being Clean Green Certified since 2011.

programme.title: Meet the International Canna Farmer's Association Chair, Kristin Nevedal
programme.desc: We're honored to welcome to today's show, Kristin Nevedal, International Cannabis Farmer's Association Chair. The International Cannabis Farmer’s Association strives to empower traditional Cannabis farmers through education, research and advocacy. Their programs raise public awareness about the benefits of traditionally farmed Cannabis and provide educational resources for farmers, regulators, industry and consumers. They advocate for the development of responsible regulations in CA, which are seen as crucially important due to the state’s significance to national and international policy development. They will promote public policy that ensures an equal share of licenses are issued to traditional sun grown Cannabis farmers. They conduct research to quantify the ecological superiority of traditionally farmed Cannabis as well as gathering data necessary to establish internationally recognized appellations of origin. They create a dynamic and creative consumer direct educational campaign that highlights the quality and ecological superiority of traditionally farmed sun grown Cannabis.

programme.title: What's It Like to Judge The Emerald Cup - Go Backstage with Swami Select
programme.desc: Founded in 2003, Northern California’s Emerald Cup advances the concept of sustainable, outdoor farming of medical cannabis. Longtime advocates of the spiritually and physically healing potential of regeneratively-grown cannabis, Swami Select founders Nikki Lastreto and Swami Chaitanya have judged The Emerald Cup’s flower competition since the event began. As the largest, organic, outdoor, medicinal cannabis competition in the world, The Cup advances our movement by cross-pollinating cultivators, patients and patrons with scientific and agriculture experts who work across industries. Now a global movement, the community celebration honors the year’s best, sun-grown, medicinal cannabis producers.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Willy T Ribbs
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is former race car driver Willy T. Ribbs. Willy was the first African American to test a Formula One racing car and first African American to compete in the Indy 500. DL, Jasmine and Willy discuss the sport of auto racing, the lack of diversity, and the future of sport in the changing times of America.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Tiffany Cross
programme.desc: DL’s featured guest on DL Uncut is political analyst Tiffany Cross. She discusses her new book, “Say it Louder – Black Voters/White Narratives and Saving Our Democracy”.

programme.title: Ali in the Valley | Easy French Onion Soup
programme.desc: This Easy French Onion Soup is rich, comforting and so good with toasted cheesy bread for dipping! What better way to kick off Season 4 of Ali in the Valley than with a delicious decadent classic French Onion Soup. French Onion Soup is such a classic and SO easy to make! Onions are slowly caramelized until soft and sweet, simmered with beef broth, and just a touch of sugar. It’s topped with crispy croutons, loads of shredded gruyere cheese, and broiled into crispy, cheesy oblivion. So good!

programme.desc: The secret to cooking the perfect filet mignon is to combine pan searing with an oven finish. programme.title: Space Channel Exclusive- I4's Dr. Sian Proctor
programme.desc: Dr. Proctor is a geoscientist, explorer, space artist, and astronaut. She is the mission pilot for the Inspiration4 all-civilian orbital mission to space. She is also one of The Explorer’s Club 50: Fifty People Changing the World. Her motto is called Space2inspire where she encourages people to use their unique, one-of-a-kind strengths, and passion to inspire those within their reach and beyond. She believes that we need to actively strive for a J.E.D.I. space: a just, equitable, diverse, and inclusive space as we advance human spaceflight.

programme.title: Europa
programme.desc: Discovering and exploring Jupiter's most promising moon, Europa. Europa was named after a Phoenician noblewoman who was abducted by Zeus after he had transformed himself into a bull. Rather fittingly, Zeus established Europa on the island of Crete as its queen, where he had several children with her, including Minos, the legendary king of Crete. In later ages, the continent of Europe would be named after Europa.

programme.title: Jupiter
programme.desc: Jupiter is the fifth planet from our Sun and is, by far, the largest planet in the solar system – more than twice as massive as all the other planets combined. Jupiter’s stripes and swirls are actually cold, windy clouds of ammonia and water, floating in an atmosphere of hydrogen and helium. Jupiter’s iconic Great Red Spot is a giant storm bigger than Earth that has raged for hundreds of years.

programme.desc: Inspiration 4 has landed, the four amateur astronauts aboard this SpaceX Dragon Spacecraft have made history. Successfully completing the first all civilian mission to orbit the Earth.

programme.title: SpaceX FAA update
programme.desc: The four Astronauts aboard the Inspiration 4 are catching their breath, after a successful 3 day mission orbiting the Earth. Meanwhile SpaceX founders, Elon Musk maybe catching his breath too, but for different reasons.

programme.title: Space Channel News
programme.desc: Rwanda builds a Space Agency, NASA hikes their rates, building a Space Hotel and the perils of commercialization of space.

programme.title: Gas Stations in Space and Laser Satellites
programme.desc: The Space Economy Show host Meagan Crawford, Managing Partner at Space Fund covers manufacturing and gas stations in space. geostationary laser satellites and serial entrepreneur, Marc Bell.

programme.title: US Chamber of Commerce's Artemis III
programme.desc: The U.S. Chamber of Commerce in conjunction with the Huntsville-Madison County Chamber of Commerce will convene a policy discussion, “Path to Artemis III: Future of Human Deep Space Exploration,” focused on the role of Marshall Space Flight Center and greater Huntsville’s industrial capabilities in developing the necessary technology and hardware for sustained U.S. lunar operations.

programme.title: US Chamber of Commerce-Artemis III Episode 2
programme.desc: The U.S. Chamber of Commerce in conjunction with the Huntsville-Madison County Chamber of Commerce will convene a policy discussion, “Path to Artemis III: Future of Human Deep Space Exploration,” focused on the role of Marshall Space Flight Center and greater Huntsville’s industrial capabilities in developing the necessary technology and hardware for sustained U.S. lunar operations.

programme.title: Space For Humanity
programme.desc: Space for Humanity is organizing the planet’s first Sponsored Citizen Astronaut Program, where leaders, from any walk of life, can apply for an opportunity to go to space and experience the Overview Effect: the cognitive shift in awareness that occurs when a human being looks down on the Earth from space.

programme.title: Crew 2 Mission Countdown Encore Presentation
programme.desc: Space Channel takes a look at the astronauts and their mission to replace the current crew on the ISS.

programme.title: Space Channel Special: Latest News, Sian Proctor and Frank White
programme.desc: Space Channel News updates and an exclusive interview with Sian Proctor, when she was an Analog Astronaut. Also an interview with the author of The Overview Effect, Frank White.

programme.title: Walt Disney Resort Behind The Scenes
programme.desc: Since 1971, Walt Disney World has grown from a theme park and three hotels in Orlando, Florida to a vacation resort of unprecedented size and scope. Today the property encompasses four major theme parks, three water parks, 29 resort hotels, 99 holes of golf, two miniature golf courses, and more.

programme.title: Wild Travels: America's Most Unusual Festivals
programme.desc: When it is festival time, it is FUN time. Join Will Clinger and travel coast to coast to discover America’s most unique, enlightening, and unusual festivals. Get in the spirit, celebrate life, and pay homage to our shared cultural history.

programme.title: Italy: Part 1
programme.desc: Experience the arresting appeal and elegance of Italy in six select locations. Take an invigorating stroll along the Mediterranean coast in Castello Federiciano, marvel at Alberobello’s august trullo dry stone huts, and more.

programme.title: Adelaide South Australia
programme.desc: Jason visits Australia’s oldest winery in Adelaide and has a memorable dining experience in one of Australia’s top dining experiences, Restaurant Orana. For some sightseeing, he rides a bike through the sensational Barossa Valley.

programme.title: Cobra Heart-Food That Makes You Manly
programme.desc: Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam: After taking a cyclo-ride through Ho Chi Minh City and trying various foods from roadside vendors and markets, Tony tests his might with a few shots of snake wine and a live cobra heart.

programme.title: Malta
programme.desc: A delightful Mediterranean climate, fantastic beaches, and fascinating historic sites only begin to describe the Maltese experience. Few places in the world possess a more exquisite coastline. The HBO series, "Game of Thrones," filmed portions of the series in Malta's capital city of Valletta.

programme.title: Dublin
programme.desc: At the confluence of Muir Eireann and the Irish Sea on Ireland’s East Coast stands the capital city of Dublin. Join Laura McKenzie as she enjoys the perfect pint at Gravity Bar atop Guinness Brewery, explore Dublin Castle, and become acquainted with The Four Seasons Dublin.

programme.title: Paris
programme.desc: There is more than enough to keep you busy in Paris. Historic sites such as the Louvre, Notre Dame Cathedral, the Picasso Museum, and Paris Opera House only get you started. Tuileries Garden and Paris Beach offer a unique way to relax and have fun, and Sacre-Coeur offers a 360-degree view of city.

programme.title: Los Angeles
programme.desc: Rent a Rolls Royce and roll through L.A. in style. When you hit Hollywood and Vine you know you are in the city’s heart, as the Pantages Theater, Capitol Records Building, Grauman's Chinese Theatre, and Kodak Theater greet you. Get the skinny on everything Beverly Hills and visit Olvera Street.

programme.title: Prague
programme.desc: Explore the heart of Bohemia as we join Laura in Prague. Visit Prague Castle, the Charles Bridge, and the Jewish Quarter. Gothic Loket Castle is a short, scenic drive away from the city and worth the tour. Next up the must-see spa town of Karlovy Vary.

programme.title: Britain's Historic Countryside
programme.desc: First stops are Camden Market and Notting Hill Gate. Enjoy a treat as Laura escorts you to the birthplace of pomp and circumstance, Buckingham Palace. Then mosey down to Windsor Castle before taking on London with Big Ben and Tower Bridge.

programme.title: Adelaide South Australia
programme.desc: Jason visits Australia’s oldest winery in Adelaide and has a memorable dining experience in one of Australia’s top dining experiences, Restaurant Orana. For some sightseeing, he rides a bike through the sensational Barossa Valley.

programme.title: Cobra Heart-Food That Makes You Manly
programme.desc: Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam: After taking a cyclo-ride through Ho Chi Minh City and trying various foods from roadside vendors and markets, Tony tests his might with a few shots of snake wine and a live cobra heart.

programme.title: S8E6 - A Delicious Feast in Magdalena Bay
programme.desc: Rick and local guide Luis Garduno of REDTours venture out on a skiff to learn about sustainable fishing on Magdalena Bay. They catch up with local lobster fishermen and clam divers and follow that up with shore lunch on Isla de Magdalena.

programme.title: S8E7 - Cooking in Wine Country
programme.desc: Ever dream of owning a winery? Don and Tru Miller made their dreams come true when they built Adobe Guadalupe. Rick’s dream of cooking in their stunning kitchen, with its handmade wood-fired oven, comes true this season. Dream on.

programme.title: S8E8 - Tijuana Round Table
programme.desc: There is a long heritage of good food in Tijuana. The city has an amazing taco, culture and is the birthplace of the Caesar salad. Today, Tijuana boasts one of the top culinary schools in the country and some of the best chefs in Mexico.

programme.title: S8E9 - Extraordinarily Delicious Ensenada
programme.desc: Fish tacos embody Ensenada’s history: Fresh fish from pristine waters encased in crispy batter influenced by Asian immigrants, topped with Spanish-inspired creamy sauces, wrapped in a very Mexican corn tortilla, and spiked with chile.

programme.title: S8E10 - Mexican Microbrews and Pub Fare
programme.desc: Many of us experienced our first Mexican beer on a beach with a squeeze of lime. Now we are happy to see a beer revolution rumbling in the Baja peninsula. Rick takes us from the Tecate brewery to the Tijuana brewery. Salud-

programme.title: S8E11 - Sustainable Aquaculture in the Rich Waters of Ensenada
programme.desc: Two of Ensenada’s best chefs, Benito Molina, and Alain Genchi, join Rick for a lesson in mollusk farming. Juan Carlos Lapuente takes the trio to the rich coastal waters to see oyster and mussel farming and learn why these waters thrive.

programme.title: Montego Bay, Jamaica
programme.desc: Donna visits Montego Bay and Negril where she will continue her journey into the heart of Jamaica. Join her as she visits the Rose Hall Great House with its mysterious past, Half Moon Resort, and takes part in cliff diving and zip lining.

programme.title: From Chicago to the Karoo
programme.desc: A healthy mind, body, and environment are all critical for living happy and productive lives. Meet pioneering people in Iraq, Colombia, South Africa, Indonesia, the United States, and Italy who believe in living symbiotically with nature.

programme.title: From Guatemala to the Congo
programme.desc: Stewardship of the land is a central part of the human condition. Unfortunately, in some cases, so is greed. Meet people from California, Congo, India, Australia, Guatemala, and Slovenia whose spirit matches their intent to live healthily.

programme.title: Germany's Via Julia
programme.desc: Discover the ancient Roman military road Via Julia that made rapid travel from Lutetia (now Paris) to Constantinople (now Istanbul) possible. Meet the people who keep the memories of this ancient route intact, and who do their utmost to keep the sacred traditions of their ancestors alive.

programme.title: The Road of Livingstone
programme.desc: “The Road of Livingstone” is a long journey in the footsteps of the British explorer David Livingstone along the Zambezi River, from its mouth in Mozambique all the way to Victoria Falls, at the border of Zambia and Zimbabwe.

programme.title: Wild Delicacies
programme.desc: Cambodia: With a friend along for the ride, Tony travels to Phnom Penh, Cambodia, where he explores a food culture that is both pleasing to the palette and slightly frightening.

programme.title: Eating on the Edge of Nowhere
programme.desc: Cambodia and Japan: Taking his obsession with the film Apocalypse Now a little too seriously, Tony sets out for Pailin, reputed to be one of the most dangerous towns on earth. After his journey, Tony returns to Japan.

programme.title: S7E2 - Rome: Baroque Brilliance
programme.desc: As we ramble through the heart of Rome, we’ll admire breathtaking Bernini statues and ponder sunbeams inside St. Peter’s Basilica. After dinner, we’ll take a nighttime stroll, lacing together the city’s piazzas and fountains.

programme.title: S8E2 - Central Turkey
programme.desc: In Turkey, we'll marvel at the fascinating landscape of Cappadocia from high above in a balloon...and from deep below, prowling an underground city where Christians once hid out.

programme.title: Wild Travels: America's Oddest Museums
programme.desc: Museums serve a vital purpose in preserving world culture and history, and the clever museums we visit have accomplished the same objective. Walk through the doors of history and visit America’s oddest museums with your host Will Clinger.

programme.title: S8E5 - Eat Like a Local in Los Cabos
programme.desc: Ever travel to a tourist mecca and wonder what the locals eat? Join Rick and his friend Hugo to find the best Mexican food in Los Cabos. First stop is the municipal market in San Jose del Cabo, then they enjoy carnitas at Los Michoacanos.

programme.title: Catalina Island
programme.desc: Catalina Island, California is a unique island off the coast of California, and Donna will take you on a journey there to revel in the island’s history, art, cuisine, and have some fun horseback riding.

programme.title: Curbside Eats
programme.desc: Join hosts Maya Norman and Katrina Kozar as they travel in an R.V. for good food, good drink, and great conversation on Curbside Eats.

programme.title: Edinburgh and Scotland
programme.desc: Friendly and feisty, Scotland makes us feel right at home. In Edinburgh, we climb the ramparts of this city's famous castle, shop for kilts, visit mysterious Rosslyn Chapel and gasp on a ghost tour. Then we head to historic St. Andrew's to practice our swing on the world's most famous golf course.

programme.title: Barcelona and Costa Brava
programme.desc: A Mediterranean marvel, Barcelona simmers with beautiful beaches, medieval mazes, eye popping art and hypnotic architecture. From tapas bars, to surrealist art, to Modernist structures, we will feast on Barcelona's delights.

programme.title: Madrid
programme.desc: The Spanish capital Madrid welcomes us with grand plazas and sparkling fountains. First stop is the Prado, one of Europe's great museums and home to Goya, El Greco and Velazquez.

programme.title: S8E11 - Prague
programme.desc: We'll visit beautifully preserved Prague to experience its massive castle, evocative Jewish Quarter, thrilling history, infectious music...and perhaps the best beer in Europe.

programme.title: Las Vegas
programme.desc: Explore Las Vegas’ lesser known past. We visit the National Atomic Testing museum to learn about how the desert outside of Vegas was used for testing America’s secret nuclear weapons. We also visit the Mormon Fort, the first permanent non-native settlement in the area, as well as the Neon Museum.

programme.title: Belize
programme.desc: Un-Belizable! We are off on a Central American Mayan excursion. We head up the steps of the ancient high temple at Lamanai. Then we take a city tour of the main tourist destination, Belize City. We learn about Belize's colonial roots at the Belize City History Museum and dive the amazing Blue Hole.

programme.title: Melbourne Victoria
programme.desc: Jason catches his own lunch at Buxton trout farm, visits a stone fruit orchard, learns how to make sausages at The Green Olive, and learns secrets of cooking from top Australian chef, Guy Grossi.

programme.title: Stuffed like a Pig
programme.desc: Portugal & Southwest France: Visiting his boss's family farm, Tony helps slaughter and feast on a pig the family has been fattening all year. Then, Tony heads to France to experience the rich delights of a foie gras farm.

programme.title: Disneyland Resort: Behind the Scenes
programme.desc: It was Walt Disney’s original vision that Disneyland would “never be completed” – always growing and changing. Decades later, Disneyland remains one of the most visited destinations on Earth. Disney Parks has proven its ability remain relevant and continue to be at the very top of the theme parks.

programme.title: The Glacier Express and Gornergrat-Bahn
programme.desc: Go sightseeing on the Glacier Express, an extraordinary railway journey high into the Swiss Alps across 291 bridges, through 91 tunnels, and across the Oberalp Pass at the highest point (2,033 meters, or 6,670 feet, above sea level), and, visit the iconic Matterhorn on the Gornergrat-Bahn.

programme.title: Shedd Aquarium: Underwater Beauty
programme.desc: Fish of all stripes and fluorescence call the crystal-clear waters of Chicago’s Shedd Aquarium home. Water and light collaborate to reveal the tranquil beauty that is life underwater.

programme.title: Perth Western Australia
programme.desc: In Western Australia, Jason visits vineyards, goes on a food adventure for crayfishes, truffles, and finger limes, and visits a Brazilian food in Perth city.

programme.title: Eating on the Mekong
programme.desc: Mekong River, Vietnam: On the river, Tony drinks a lot of Mekong moonshine with the welcoming owners of a duck farm. Although seduced by his Vietnam experience, Tony is not sure the royal dish Birds Nest Soup is all its cracked up to be.

programme.title: San Francisco
programme.desc: Stroll down Grant Street with Laura into the heart of America's largest Chinatown. Bike, drive, or walk across the Golden Gate Bridge, the city's most recognizable landmark. Finally, Fisherman's Wharf offers day trips all wrapped into one fun location.

programme.title: Versailles
programme.desc: Enter 12 miles of enclosing walls, 26 acres of roof, and over 2,000 windows and experience the royal Palace of Versailles. If you are looking for some good ole' fun, then you will enjoy Parc Asterix. Place Vendome is the top spot for high-end merchandise.

programme.title: Gold Coast Australia
programme.desc: If you like sun, surf, sand, and a laid-back lifestyle then join Laura on Australia's Gold Coast. Travel into the thick of the Queensland Rainforest, and visit the home of the largest collection of Australian native animals in the Carrumbin Wildlife Sanctuary.

programme.title: Sicily
programme.desc: Begin on the east coast in Taormina. Laura then takes us to some of Sicily's highlight cities, Palermo and Randazzo. How about a visit to Agrigento, or to the divinely inspired Cathedral Monreale? We will also visit Mt. Etna, an active volcano.

programme.title: Venice
programme.desc: Begin with a tour down the Grand Canal, "the finest street in the world." Next, the pedestrian streets around the Rialto Bridge are lined with shops, and St. Mark's Basilica is one of the oldest and most beautiful Byzantine cathedrals in all of Europe.

programme.title: Oahu, Hawaii
programme.desc: Have a blast with Laura on this Hawaiian voyage as you explore sensational surf and beaches, unique Hawaiian culture and food, and climb volcanic mountains. Join Laura as she visits historic landmarks, such as the Iolani Palace and the Bishop Museum.

programme.title: Perth Western Australia
programme.desc: In Western Australia, Jason visits vineyards, goes on a food adventure for crayfishes, truffles, and finger limes, and visits a Brazilian food in Perth city.

programme.title: Eating on the Mekong
programme.desc: Mekong River, Vietnam: On the river, Tony drinks a lot of Mekong moonshine with the welcoming owners of a duck farm. Although seduced by his Vietnam experience, Tony is not sure the royal dish Birds Nest Soup is all its cracked up to be.

programme.title: S9E1 - Oaxaca's Most Magical Holiday
programme.desc: Rick takes us on a remarkable journey through Oaxaca City during the revered Dia de Los Muertos (Day of the Dead) holiday. Much preparation for the celebration takes place in October, and Rick gives us an insider’s look at the fiesta.

programme.title: S9E2 - Oaxaca's Live-Fire Cooking
programme.desc: Everything tastes better when cooked over a fire, at least that is the Oaxacan credo. From soup to barbacoa, fiery embers influence the flavor of Oaxaca’s food in just the right ways. Join Rick in Oaxaca, San Felipe Usila, and Zaachilla.

programme.title: S9E3 - Off the Beaten Path in Huatulco
programme.desc: Mexico's beaches glimmer with pristine perfection. Chef Rick Bayless takes us off the beaten path to find great food and even better beaches such as Playa Chahue and Playa Principal. You would be well-advised to follow his lead.

programme.title: S9E4 - Artisan Mescal
programme.desc: Mescal is experiencing a renaissance in Mexico and throughout the United States. Journey with Rick to witness firsthand how an Oaxacan distiller handcrafts this fine spirit renowned for its rich, smoky complexity and brightness.

programme.title: S9E5 - Oaxaca, the Land of Seven Moles
programme.desc: So many moles, so little time. Rick will focus on two moles while visiting the Seasons of My Heart Cooking School on the outskirts of Oaxaca City to explore Black Mole and Green Mole with school owner Susana Trilling and her students.

programme.title: S9E6 - Delicious Eco-Tourism
programme.desc: Ever on a quest to learn more about food, Rick even vacations with a food-oriented agenda. Join him in the mountains of Finca Las Nieves, with its artisanal coffee production and organic gardens, and learn about sustainable gardening.

programme.title: Montreal, Canada
programme.desc: Join Donna in Montreal and experience the cultural and Epicurean wonders found in this amazing city in Quebec. Also, go jet boating and learn why Montreal is the unofficial "world headquarters" for the circus arts.

programme.title: From Ithaca to the Amazon
programme.desc: Our natural environments are intrinsically more valuable than any grand visions of wealth created using methods detrimental to the Earth. Meet people in New York, India, Russia, Peru, Sumatra, and South Africa who favor health over profit.

programme.title: From Hanoi to Paris
programme.desc: The value of Earth’s natural resources changes depending on to whom you speak. Meet people from France, Colombia, Vietnam, South Africa, the Philippines, and Michigan who have circumvented extraordinary challenges to protect the Earth.

programme.title: Italy's Via Cassia
programme.desc: Italy’s Via Cassia once led north from Rome to Florence, finally joining the Via Aurelia at Luna (now Luni). As you meander northward along the ancient route, each unique location you visit, and the interesting people you meet there, speak vividly to the region’s steeped history and culture.

programme.title: Cuba
programme.desc: Cuba is a Caribbean Hotspot. The island is a combination of gorgeous landscapes and a unique way of life. Travel from the Guanahacabibes Peninsula to Guantanamo. In Havana, meet students that wonder about their future prospects: exile or revolution?

programme.title: Childhood Flavors
programme.desc: Arcachon, France: Here, Bourdain first learned to love food as a child. Returning for a trip down memory lane, Tony enjoys childhood staples, including steak frites, gaufres (waffles), soupe de pecheur (fisherman's soup) and fresh oysters.

programme.title: Stuffed like a Pig
programme.desc: Portugal & Southwest France: Visiting his boss's family farm, Tony helps slaughter and feast on a pig the family has been fattening all year. Then, Tony heads to France to experience the rich delights of a foie gras farm.

programme.title: S7E3 - Rome: Back-Street Riches
programme.desc: We explore Rome on a more intimate scale — dodging Vespas in Trastevere, roaming through the historic Jewish Ghetto, and enjoying art treasures in a string of rarely visited churches to uncover the charms of hidden Rome.

programme.title: S8E3 - France’s Loire: Chateau Country
programme.desc: In France's Loire Valley, we'll visit four unique castles — elegant Chenonceau, massive Chambord, stately Cheverny, and fragrant Villandry — with fun stops along the way.

programme.title: Wild Travels: America's Oddest Museums
programme.desc: Museums serve a vital purpose in preserving world culture and history, and the clever museums we visit have accomplished the same objective. Walk through the doors of history and visit America’s oddest museums with your host Will Clinger.

programme.title: S9E7 - The Kernel of Deliciousness
programme.desc: The variety of corns available in Oaxaca boggles the mind and the taste buds. Rick introduces us to Amado Ramirez Leyva who believes that corn, domesticated some 9,000 years ago in Mexico, represents the very foundation of Mexican culture.

programme.title: Curbside Eats
programme.desc: Join hosts Maya Norman and Katrina Kozar as they travel in an R.V. for good food, good drink, and great conversation on Curbside Eats.

programme.title: Edmonton, Canada
programme.desc: In the second part of her tour of Alberta, Canada, you and Donna will discover fresh cuisine at the local farmer's market and explore some of the region’s crafts. You will also go snowshoeing and learn how to ski.

programme.title: France's Normandy
programme.desc: From a dramatic coast to rural pastures, this sweet section of France abounds with apple orchards, enchanting villages, stunning abbeys, and sparkling seaports. We base in the lovely seaside town Honfleur. At Giverny, and in the museums in Rouen and Honfleur, we discover the birth of Impressionism.

programme.title: Medieval Europe
programme.desc: The medieval world is one of the big draws of European Travel. Moody ruins, "tippy" towers, cobbled streets, sparkling mosaics, monasteries, castles, and cathedrals form the core of many a tourist's dreams. In this episode, we make sense out of a fascinating 1,000 years of history.

programme.title: Four Great Cities of Europe
programme.desc: Explore the world class European cities of London, Paris, Amsterdam, and Brussels. A European city bustles. It is a hub of commerce, the arts, energy, surprise, and international flavor. Where do you start if you have just 24-hours?

programme.title: S8E10 - The Netherlands: Beyond Amsterdam
programme.desc: Zipping from Haarlem to Rotterdam, and from Delft to the former Zuiderzee, we'll enjoy fragrant cheese markets, soggy polderland, charming towns, and windmills both new and old.

programme.title: Key West
programme.desc: We are on island time for this episode. Learn about the Key's treasure hunting history at the Mel Fisher Museum. Explore Fort Jefferson, an isolated fort in the Gulf of Mexico that defended the islands. American literature enthusiasts will enjoy a look at Ernest Hemingway's Key West home.

programme.title: Louisville
programme.desc: And we are off! We learn the history of the world famous Kentucky Derby, and call our shot, at one of America's most famous brands, Louisville Slugger. Also, we zip line in the world's only underground zip line attraction, and learn about Muhammad Ali's legacy at the Ali Center.

programme.title: Hobart Tasmaina
programme.desc: In Tasmania, Jason immerses himself into the natural world by visiting Cradle Mountain and Weindorfer’s Forest Walk. He also experiences Hobart's cafe culture, and goes on the hunt for fresh seafood.

programme.title: A Desert Feast
programme.desc: Morocco (Sahara): Tony traverses the Moroccan desert with one goal in mind, to eat a mud-oven-roasted sheep.

programme.title: Ultimate Walt Disney World
programme.desc: Disney Parks are known for their unparalleled attractions, resorts, and vacation experiences, but when you think of Disney, do you think faced-paced, action-packed, adrenaline-pumping experiences? From the Tower of Terror to Mission Space, and Expedition Everest to Toy Story Mania, get “ultimate.”

programme.title: Wild Travels: America's Most Unusual Festivals
programme.desc: When it is festival time, it is FUN time. Join Will Clinger and travel coast to coast to discover America’s most unique, enlightening, and unusual festivals. Get in the spirit, celebrate life, and pay homage to our shared cultural history.

programme.title: Italy: Part 2
programme.desc: The brilliance and grandeur of Italy is demonstrated in five captivating settings. Feel like a tall wildflower in the sun and breeze as the hills of Altomonte billow off into the distance, sooth every aching nerve as you absorb the perfect view along the Tiber River, and more.

programme.title: Hobart Tasmaina
programme.desc: In Tasmania, Jason immerses himself into the natural world by visiting Cradle Mountain and Weindorfer’s Forest Walk. He also experiences Hobart's cafe culture, and goes on the hunt for fresh seafood.

programme.title: Wild Delicacies
programme.desc: Cambodia: With a friend along for the ride, Tony travels to Phnom Penh, Cambodia, where he explores a food culture that is both pleasing to the palette and slightly frightening.

programme.title: Walt Disney Resort Behind The Scenes
programme.desc: Since 1971, Walt Disney World has grown from a theme park and three hotels in Orlando, Florida to a vacation resort of unprecedented size and scope. Today the property encompasses four major theme parks, three water parks, 29 resort hotels, 99 holes of golf, two miniature golf courses, and more.

programme.title: Disneyland Resort: Behind the Scenes
programme.desc: It was Walt Disney’s original vision that Disneyland would “never be completed” – always growing and changing. Decades later, Disneyland remains one of the most visited destinations on Earth. Disney Parks has proven its ability remain relevant and continue to be at the very top of the theme parks.

programme.title: Ultimate Walt Disney World
programme.desc: Disney Parks are known for their unparalleled attractions, resorts, and vacation experiences, but when you think of Disney, do you think faced-paced, action-packed, adrenaline-pumping experiences? From the Tower of Terror to Mission Space, and Expedition Everest to Toy Story Mania, get “ultimate.”

programme.title: Hobart Tasmaina
programme.desc: In Tasmania, Jason immerses himself into the natural world by visiting Cradle Mountain and Weindorfer’s Forest Walk. He also experiences Hobart's cafe culture, and goes on the hunt for fresh seafood.

programme.title: Wild Delicacies
programme.desc: Cambodia: With a friend along for the ride, Tony travels to Phnom Penh, Cambodia, where he explores a food culture that is both pleasing to the palette and slightly frightening.

programme.title: S9E5 - Oaxaca, the Land of Seven Moles
programme.desc: So many moles, so little time. Rick will focus on two moles while visiting the Seasons of My Heart Cooking School on the outskirts of Oaxaca City to explore Black Mole and Green Mole with school owner Susana Trilling and her students.

programme.title: S9E6 - Delicious Eco-Tourism
programme.desc: Ever on a quest to learn more about food, Rick even vacations with a food-oriented agenda. Join him in the mountains of Finca Las Nieves, with its artisanal coffee production and organic gardens, and learn about sustainable gardening.

programme.title: S9E7 - The Kernel of Deliciousness
programme.desc: The variety of corns available in Oaxaca boggles the mind and the taste buds. Rick introduces us to Amado Ramirez Leyva who believes that corn, domesticated some 9,000 years ago in Mexico, represents the very foundation of Mexican culture.

programme.title: S9E8 - Mercado Madness
programme.desc: “You are what you eat.” Brillat Savarin’s statement fuels Rick’s tour of the 21 de Noviembre market in downtown Oaxaca. We uncover the incredibly rich culture of the market and its role in the daily lives and meals of the local population.

programme.title: S9E9 - Oaxacan Cheese Primer
programme.desc: In Mexico, cheese is all about freshness, and fresh cheese is exactly what Rick has found in the village of Rojas where he and two local women turn uber-fresh milk from alfalfa-fed cows into queso fresco and salty quesillo (string cheese).

programme.title: S9E10 - Puerto Escondido: Living the Dream
programme.desc: Ever dream of renting a space with a kitchen in Mexico just to cook all the fresh fish you can eat? Rick lives the dream at Hotel Villas Carrizalillo in Puerto Escondido. With few culinary tools, and fresh ingredients, it is time to feast.

programme.title: Catalina Island
programme.desc: Catalina Island, California is a unique island off the coast of California, and Donna will take you on a journey there to revel in the island’s history, art, cuisine, and have some fun horseback riding.

programme.title: From Myanmar to Scotland
programme.desc: Biodiversity is a central component to the successful operation of Earth’s natural systems. Meet people from Haiti, Myanmar, Honduras, Kenya, Canada, and Scotland who spend time and energy securing healthy local environmental regulations.

programme.title: From Liberia to Mongolia
programme.desc: What we take from and put back into the Earth reflects the very nature of who we are as human beings. Meet people from Washington, Liberia, Macedonia, the Cook Islands, Mongolia, and Chile who believe end results depend upon how we begin.

programme.title: France's Via Aquitania
programme.desc: Follow the Via Aquitania, an ancient Roman road that connected a network of cities and was the main trade route between the Mediterranean Sea and the Atlantic Ocean. Traces of the region’s history abound and will become clearer to you the more you hear the people who love this land speak of it.

programme.title: The Route of the Two Oceans
programme.desc: The thin ridge that links the two Americas is a miniature world unto itself and concentrates a vast amount of diversity into a small area of land. Follow the Inter-American Highway from Panama City to the Isthmus of Rivas in Nicaragua, the narrowest ridge of Central America.

programme.title: The Cook Who Came in From the Cold
programme.desc: St. Petersburg, Russia: Tony plays spy in Russia and sets off to locate the best blinis and borscht St. Petersburg has to offer.

programme.title: So Much Vodka, So Little Time
programme.desc: St. Petersburg, Russia: Tony continues his mission with a tour of local working-class specialties. He tries his hand at ice-fishing, drinks a lot of vodka, feasts on Russian foods, eats smoked fish and ends the outing with a dip in the outdoor cold pool.

programme.title: S7E4 - Florence: Heart of the Renaissance
programme.desc: In Florence, we'll revel in the genius of Michelangelo and Botticelli, climb the dome that kicked off the Renaissance, and cross the Arno to take in modern-day artisan life.

programme.title: S8E4 - Paris Side Trips
programme.desc: After roaming Versailles — the palace of palaces — we'll drop in on exquisite Vaux-le-Vicomte and extravagant Fontainebleau, marvel at Chartres Cathedral...and dine like kings.

programme.title: Wild Travels: America's Oddest Museums
programme.desc: Museums serve a vital purpose in preserving world culture and history, and the clever museums we visit have accomplished the same objective. Walk through the doors of history and visit America’s oddest museums with your host Will Clinger.

programme.title: Curbside Eats
programme.desc: Join hosts Maya Norman and Katrina Kozar as they travel in an R.V. for good food, good drink, and great conversation on Curbside Eats.

programme.title: S8E10 - Mexican Microbrews and Pub Fare
programme.desc: Many of us experienced our first Mexican beer on a beach with a squeeze of lime. Now we are happy to see a beer revolution rumbling in the Baja peninsula. Rick takes us from the Tecate brewery to the Tijuana brewery. Salud-

programme.title: Singapore
programme.desc: Join Donna and visit a jewel of an Asian country- Singapore. Experience a place that weaves a confluence of cultures into its fabric, evident in the city’s unique cuisine. Witness acrobat training, explore the fine art of tea, and more.

programme.title: Edinburgh and Scotland
programme.desc: Friendly and feisty, Scotland makes us feel right at home. In Edinburgh, we climb the ramparts of this city's famous castle, shop for kilts, visit mysterious Rosslyn Chapel and gasp on a ghost tour. Then we head to historic St. Andrew's to practice our swing on the world's most famous golf course.

programme.title: Barcelona and Costa Brava
programme.desc: A Mediterranean marvel, Barcelona simmers with beautiful beaches, medieval mazes, eye popping art and hypnotic architecture. From tapas bars, to surrealist art, to Modernist structures, we will feast on Barcelona's delights.

programme.title: Madrid
programme.desc: The Spanish capital Madrid welcomes us with grand plazas and sparkling fountains. First stop is the Prado, one of Europe's great museums and home to Goya, El Greco and Velazquez.

programme.title: S8E9 - Amsterdam
programme.desc: Uniquely entertaining Amsterdam shows off its Rembrandts and Van Goghs, rivers of bikes, and pot-filled coffeeshops — all under gabled facades leaning out over placid canals.

programme.title: Savannah
programme.desc: We visit the old South and enjoy some sweet tea in Savannah. On this episode, we will stroll the city’s beautiful squares, as well as visit its civil war past at Old Fort Jackson. Then, we head up the stairs of the famous Tybee Island lighthouse and visit the Savannah Railroad museum.

programme.title: New Orleans
programme.desc: The saints come marching in as we tour the New Orlean's iconic St. Louis Cathedral and the mysterious Ursuline Convent. We see how floats are made and delve into Mardi Gras history at Mardi Gras World. Finally, we visit the National World War II Museum's world-class collection of memorabilia.

programme.title: Perth Western Australia
programme.desc: In Western Australia, Jason visits vineyards, goes on a food adventure for crayfishes, truffles, and finger limes, and visits a Brazilian food in Perth city.

programme.title: Traditional Tastes
programme.desc: Morocco (Cities): Tony is invited to experience the culinary heart and distinct walled medinas (districts) of the Moroccan city Fes.

programme.title: Disney Animal Kingdom
programme.desc: Explore the process of designing and creating Disney’s Animal Kingdom with incredible behind-the-scenes footage. Discover how Disney incorporates live animals into their attractions and uncover the time taken to create authentic habitats that allow visitors to experience a safari or jungle trek.

programme.desc: From blood sausage to chewy ginger cakes, Andrew explores Louisiana's Cajun country.

programme.desc: Explore the collision of cultures that gave birth to America's diverse musical heritage.

programme.title: America. The Beautiful.: The Caribbean
programme.desc: A cave explorer battles a dangerous underground river in Puerto Rico.

programme.desc: For over 130 years, Nashville has been at the forefront of the music scene. From the 1800s when the Fisk Jubilee Singers traveled the continent, to Johnny Cash, to The Black Keys, this is a special place with a story to tell.

programme.title: Book 6: The Ship of Adventure (Part 2)

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - An Unforgettable Trip, South Lake, Part Two
programme.desc: This show was filmed in late October of 2019. Four months prior, in June of 2019, Tim Carnahan was diagnosed with Glioblastoma, Brain Cancer. According to Tim's medical team, his life expectancy could be between three months and 18 months. Fast forward to now, 2020; today's update is one we hoped would never come. With a heavy heart and tear-filled eyes, we share with you that Tim Carnahan has passed away after battling for close to 12 months. It only fits that the last words to pass his lips were I love you, Lory, and keep fishing. While his time on earth was cut short, the amount of joy he experienced and shared with others was genuinely tremendous and will never be forgotten. If you would like to help out in any way, lory and friends have put together a Go Fund Me page to ease the financial burden of medical bills and afford lory some time to greave and transition into life without Tim. We love you, Tim. Rest in peace, buddy.

programme.desc: This show was filmed in late October of 2019. Four months prior, in June of 2019, Tim Carnahan was diagnosed with Glioblastoma, Brain Cancer. With a heavy heart and tear-filled eyes, we share with you that Tim Carnahan has passed away after battling for close to 12 months. It only fits that the last words to pass his lips were I love you, Lory, and keep fishing. While his time on earth was cut short, the amount of joy he experienced and shared with others was genuinely tremendous and will never be forgotten. If you would like to help out in any way, lory and friends have put together a Go Fund Me page to ease the financial burden of medical bills and afford lory some time to greave and transition into life without Tim. We love you, Tim. Rest in peace, buddy.

Long days on the water navigating the complex tangles of river channels and beaver dams, and a grueling portage around Robinson Falls, bring the team to the brink of collapse.
